Sentencas: MCuCo40(CuCo-CeO2, 40 at.% metal load, 1/1 Cu-Co atomic ratio), synthesised by inverse microemulsion method, was evaluated as the anode for SOFC at intermediate temperature.
Titulo: Effect of cobalt incorporation in copper-ceria based anodes for hydrocarbon utilisation in Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: This material presents optimal physicochemical and electrical characteristics as well as excellent thermal and chemical compatibility with 8YSZ electrolyte.
Titulo: Effect of cobalt incorporation in copper-ceria based anodes for hydrocarbon utilisation in Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The evaluation of single-cell performance, with 8YSZ electrolyte and LSM cathode and this anode material, operating in H-2 and methane fuels, in comparison with a similar single-cell using Cu-ceria-based anode allows to conclude that the substitution of copper (20 at.%) by cobalt in the anode composition enhances the single cell performance as well as reduces the carbon deposit formation on the anode after running on hydrocarbon fuels (methane).
Titulo: Effect of cobalt incorporation in copper-ceria based anodes for hydrocarbon utilisation in Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
